14th Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 117th Street, showing two views of a late nineteenth century private home. It was owned in 1873 by J. H. Rauch and in 1891 by O. Roesingle. 14th Avenue, here, was then known as First Avenue.

P. L. Sperr

March 13, 1932
Views 1,2
